episodes.title: The baptism of Jason Struhs - and how it led to the death of his daughter Elizabeth
episodes.description:
In late January, a Queensland supreme court judge issued his verdict on the death of eight-year-old Toowoomba girl Elizabeth Struhs.
Subscribe to Guardian Australia on YouTube and hit the bell to see new videos ► http://bit.ly/gdnaustraliasubs

He found Brendan Stevens, the leader of a religious sect known as the Saints, and Elizabeth's father, Jason Struhs, not guilty of murder. But he did find them guilty of manslaughter, along with 12 other members of the Saints. In Jason's case, the court found that his religious faith was so strong, he believed Elizabeth would be saved by a miracle.

episodes.title: Fourteen members of religious sect found guilty of killing eight-year-old Elizabeth Struhs
episodes.description:
A Queensland supreme court justice has found 14 members of a Toowoomba religious sect known as the Saints guilty of manslaughter of eight-year-old Elizabeth Struhs, by denying her the insulin she needed to treat her type 1 diabetes. 
Subscribe to Guardian Australia on YouTube and hit the bell to see new videos ► http://bit.ly/gdnaustraliasubs
 
Elizabeth's father, Jason, and the leader of the Saints, Brendan Stevens, were found not guilty of murder. 
 
Elizabeth died at her family home in Rangeville, Toowoomba, west of Brisbane, on 6 or 7 January 2022, allegedly of diabetic ketoacidosis. The Saints members on trial refused to participate in many elements of the trial, by refusing counsel and not entering pleas. They argued the prosecution was a form of religious persecution

episodes.title: Police video shows cult leader and partner arrested over alleged historical child grooming
episodes.description:
Sex crimes squad detectives have charged two people following an investigation into alleged historical child grooming under Strike Force Gandell. Cult leader William Kamm and his partner were arrested in Sydney over allegations they groomed a 19-year-old woman for sex from the age of six.
